This paper deals with image feature selection using a genetic algorithm, which is a common technique in computer vision and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on homography estimation, which is a subfield of computer vision related to image registration and geometric transformations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the use of evolutionary algorithms and spatial statistics suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.GR (Graphics), and cs.RO (Robotics).
